        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 4:59PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 458 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Shawsville, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Salem...
Christiansburg...
Catawba...
Shawsville...
Sinking Creek...
Bent Mountain...
and Glenvar.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
